            "title": "Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing beats Q1 top-line and bottom-line estimates",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company <a href=\"https://pr.tsmc.com/english/news/3297\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">press release</a>  (TSM): Q1  GAAP EPADR of $3.49 <font color=\"green\"> beats by $0.11</font>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $35.9B (+40.6% Y/Y) <font color=\"green\"> beats by $410M</font>.</li>\n<li>In the first quarter, shipments of 3-nanometer accounted for 25% of total wafer revenue; 5- nanometer accounted for 36%; 7-nanometer accounted for 13%. Advanced technologies, defined as 7-nanometer and more advanced technologies, accounted for 74% of total wafer revenue</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
